=== 2016年里约奥运会 ===
麥克·霍爾頓贏得[[里约奥运会|里约奥运会]]400米自由泳金牌，在賽後媒體採訪時，声称自己「只是打敗了『吃禁藥』的對手」，并声称在比赛中获得亚军的中國選手[[孙杨|孙杨]]为“服[[体育禁药|药]]的骗子”。他称自己并非针对孙杨，只是对药检阳性的运动员不满。之後麥克再度受訪時表示，「孙杨藥檢曾被驗出使用禁藥是事實」、「運動界對於禁藥應該採取零容忍政策」<ref>{{cite web|title='Sun Yang is just the drug cheat': Aussie Mack Horton slams Chinese rival after getting the ultimate revenge and beating him to win Rio gold... and urges other athletes to 'name and shame' dopers|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3727368/Rio-Olympics-Mack-Horton-calls-Sun-Yang-drug-cheat-ahead-400m-final.html|date=2016-08-06|accessdate=2016-08-06|archive-date=2016-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806232538/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3727368/Rio-Olympics-Mack-Horton-calls-Sun-Yang-drug-cheat-ahead-400m-final.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

不过麥克·霍爾頓也承认，他使用极具挑衅性的“骗子”来称呼对手孙杨，这是由於他在賽前長期採取的策略，在心理上刻意貶低對手而舒緩自身的壓力，才會在賽後訪問將貶低對手的言語脫口而出<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/sport/olympics/rio-2016/olympics-swimming/mack-hortons-stirring-gold-medal-win-a-mental-sting-as-well-as-a-physical-triumph-20160807-gqmskm.html|title=Rio Olympics 2016: Mack Horton's stirring gold medal win a mental sting as well as a physical triumph|publisher=Sydney Morning Herald|author=Phil Lutton|accessdate=2016-08-09|date=2016-08-07|archive-date=2016-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808140154/http://www.smh.com.au/sport/olympics/rio-2016/olympics-swimming/mack-hortons-stirring-gold-medal-win-a-mental-sting-as-well-as-a-physical-triumph-20160807-gqmskm.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/07/mack-horton-and-relay-team-get-australia-off-to-golden-start-in-rio-pool|title=Mack Horton and relay team get Australia off to golden start in Rio pool|work=The Guardian|date=2016-08-07|accessdate=2016-08-09|archive-date=2016-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807033659/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/07/mack-horton-and-relay-team-get-australia-off-to-golden-start-in-rio-pool|dead-url=no}}</ref>。孫楊對此回應稱「这是澳大利亚人的小伎俩，每一位能够来到奥运会的选手都应该受到尊重」<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sports.sina.com.cn/others/swim/2016-08-07/doc-ifxutfpc4694142.shtml|title=孙杨回击霍顿：澳洲小伎俩 每个选手都值得尊重|publisher=新浪体育|date=2016-08-07|accessdate=2016-08-07|archive-date=2016-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821121205/http://sports.sina.com.cn/others/swim/2016-08-07/doc-ifxutfpc4694142.shtml|dead-url=no}}</ref>。中国游泳协会认为霍尔顿此番言论「缺乏素养和体育道德」，要求澳大利亚游泳协会对此事道歉。<ref name=Guardian/>

[[国际奥委会|国际奥委会]]发言人马克·亚当斯（Mark Adams）8月8日就霍爾頓的争议言论表态称：“虽然我们鼓励[[言论自由|言论自由]]的立场很清楚，但另一方面，奥运攸关尊重他人及尊重他人竞赛的权利。每个状况当然有不同原因，但任何事都有底线，就是人们享有平静比赛的自由。”他同时表示国际奥委会不会对此事件展开深入调查。<ref name=Guardian>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/09/australia-refuses-to-apologise-for-mack-hortons-sun-yang-drug-comment|title=Australia refuses to apologise for Mack Horton's Sun Yang 'drug cheat' comment|work=The Guardian|date=2016-08-08|accessdate=2016-08-09|archive-date=2016-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809003110/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/aug/09/australia-refuses-to-apologise-for-mack-hortons-sun-yang-drug-comment|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=rfichinese>{{cite web|url=http://cn.rfi.fr/wire/20160809-%E6%BE%B3%E6%B3%B3%E5%B0%86%E9%85%B8%E5%A4%A7%E9%99%86%E5%AD%99%E6%9D%A8-ioc%E8%AE%B2%E8%AF%9D%E4%BA%86|title=澳泳将酸大陆孙杨 IOC讲话了|publisher=法国国际广播电台|agency=法新社|date=2016-08-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160809113415/http://cn.rfi.fr/wire/20160809-%E6%BE%B3%E6%B3%B3%E5%B0%86%E9%85%B8%E5%A4%A7%E9%99%86%E5%AD%99%E6%9D%A8-ioc%E8%AE%B2%E8%AF%9D%E4%BA%86|archivedate=2016-08-09|accessdate=2016-08-09}}</ref>

澳大利亚游泳协会认为霍爾頓擁有自由表达意见的权利，称“澳大利亚游泳队的价值观鼓励‘表达自己’”，认为他有权表达自己对无禁药“干净体育”的观点，同时不认为是歧视故拒绝向中国游泳队道歉。<ref name=Guardian/>

=== 2019年游泳世锦赛 ===
2019年7月21日，中国游泳运动员[[孙杨|孙杨]]夺得[[2019年世界游泳锦标赛|2019年世界游泳锦标赛]]男子400米自由泳冠军。在颁奖典礼上，孙杨与季军获得者、意大利游泳运动员[[加布里埃萊·德蒂|德蒂]]一同站上领奖台，唯独亚军获得者霍顿拒绝上台，不与孙杨合影，被认为是表达对前一年发生的孙杨干预兴奋剂检测事件及国际游泳联合会对此事处理的不满。随后在新闻发布会上，孙杨回应此事时表示：“在颁奖的时候，我想这是非常神圣的，每个人站在上面是代表自己的国家，你可以不尊重我，但你必须尊重中国。”<ref name=A>{{cite news |title=孙杨回应霍顿无礼行为：你可以不尊重我，但你必须尊重中国 |url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_3971599 |accessdate=2019-07-21 |work=澎湃新闻 |date=2019-07-21 |archive-date=2019-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721130523/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_3971599 |dead-url=no }}</ref>霍顿在赛后接受媒体集中采访时表示：“我就是不想和做那种事的人一起站上领奖台。”此外霍顿还鼓动德蒂也不站上领奖台，但遭到拒绝<ref>{{cite news |author1=news.com.au |title=Mack Horton podium protest: Bronze medallist declined request to take part |url=https://www.news.com.au/sport/more-sports/mack-horton-podium-protest-bronze-medallist-declined-request-to-take-part/news-story/72e103e8471bc72c88ecfef8ac74dfa0 |accessdate=2019-07-22 |date=2019-07-22 |archive-date=2019-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722021253/https://www.news.com.au/sport/more-sports/mack-horton-podium-protest-bronze-medallist-declined-request-to-take-part/news-story/72e103e8471bc72c88ecfef8ac74dfa0 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

针对霍顿颁奖典礼抗议一事，国际游泳联合会发表声明称已以书面的形式警告霍顿和澳大利亚游泳管理机构<ref>{{cite web|url=https://olympics.nbcsports.com/2019/07/22/mack-horton-sun-yang-swimming-protest/|title=Mack Horton applauded in athlete dining hall, warned by FINA for Sun Yang protest|publisher=NBC Olympic|date=2019-07-22|accessdate=2019-07-22|archive-date=2019-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722142434/https://olympics.nbcsports.com/2019/07/22/mack-horton-sun-yang-swimming-protest/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。後來，由於英國選手[[鄧肯·斯科特|鄧肯·斯科特]]在男子200米自由泳頒獎典禮上同樣不與孫楊合影，國際游泳聯合會警告各國選手颁奖台上不得有不尊重行為，否則將面臨至輕則警告，重則罰款甚至沒收獎牌、禁賽處分。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://swimswam.com/fina-reportedly-threatens-bans-and-revocation-of-medals-over-podium-protests/|title=FINA Reportedly Threatens Bans and Revocation of Medals Over Podium Protests|work=SwimSwam|date=2019-07-24|accessdate=2020-03-05|archive-date=2019-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190725074406/https://swimswam.com/fina-reportedly-threatens-bans-and-revocation-of-medals-over-podium-protests/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

世锦赛后，[[澳大利亚奥林匹克委员会|澳大利亚奥林匹克委员会]]对该国的运动员发出警告，要求运动员勿将[[2020年夏季奥林匹克运动会|2020年东京奥运]]颁奖典礼作为个人抗议的场所<ref>{{cite web|url=https://swimswam.com/australian-olympic-committee-warns-athletes-against-podium-protests-in-tokyo/|title=Australian Olympic Committee Warns Athletes Against Podium Protests in Tokyo|work=SwimSwam|date=2019-08-31|accessdate=2020-03-01|archive-date=2020-03-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301055442/https://swimswam.com/australian-olympic-committee-warns-athletes-against-podium-protests-in-tokyo/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

